IV. THE PIPELINE, GRELOD, AND THE FUSE
=====================================================================
HONORHALL is not charity — it is a crime pipeline. Grelod ran it: orphans trained into
Guild talent (best pickpockets in the Rift start at Honorhall), Brynjolf handling
placement, Maven handling protection. Constance Michel did the real caring while Grelod
took the credit and did the "other" work. (Warrens/Ratway intel; honor hall doc.)

WHAT THE PARTY DID (Ch.24): Orion, on his first kill-by-decision, drove Alfonso (a
telekinetically-controlled rapier) through Grelod's heart — a plain STAB-MURDER. The same
strike detonated Alfonso's living plague through Honorhall (children, Constance, the
responding guards), but that plague is still INCUBATING — asymptomatic for now. So the
scene reads RIGHT NOW as a clean assassination of a beloved saint; the outbreak surfaces
later. Orion got out clean — no witness placed him AT HONORHALL.

THE MAVEN FUSE — SHE ALREADY HOLDS EVERYTHING (discovery is ASSEMBLY, not investigation):
  MAVEN'S SIDE — via SILENCING THE HAYLOFT GIRL (Ch.22): silencing did not erase the
  girl's testimony, it transferred it into Maven's PRIVATE files. That testimony:
    - The Lanterns stab-kill and cover up in her city (the homeless woman, the stable boy).
    - The homeless woman was killed the SAME WAY as Grelod — Orion + a rapier-stab — so
      Grelod's MO MATCHES a killing Maven already has on file.
    - Orion feeds like a vampire (the girl saw the alley feed) — vampire tell #1.
  THE GUILD'S SIDE (= Maven's) — via THE RATWAY BOOK-COLLATERAL BEAT (ch.20/21 Flagon):
    - Orion put up his Cyrodiilic-vampire book ("Debate with the Undead," from Falkreath,
      ch.6/7) as collateral to BRYNJOLF, under a cover story of wanting to TRAIN UNDER
      GRELOD. That effectively told the Guild ORION IS A VAMPIRE — vampire tell #2, an
      independent source. Brynjolf dealt with him as a Maven-Lantern but was cautious
      enough to demand collateral at all.
    - The pretext got Orion DEFINITIVE confirmation of Grelod's pipeline role.
    - A day later Orion reclaimed the book ("changed his mind"); Grelod died THAT NIGHT.
      Brynjolf let the book go without a fight — the book was never the real collateral;
      the Guild kept the vampire-knowledge, which is worth far more.
  => Nothing left to DISCOVER. The fuse waits only on Maven's ATTENTION turning hostile —
     most naturally, the party handing her a fresh reason. And it is all PRIVATE knowledge
     (ammunition in her hand), never a public case. Maven now holds Orion's vampirism as
     private leverage — a hand on a secret he cannot afford exposed.

