V. DIRGE, RETALIATION, AND THE BLACKMAIL COUNTER-PLAY
=====================================================================
DIRGE (Maven's Guild enforcer, the Ratway chokepoint sentry): when Maven's attention
turns and she assembles what she holds, she sends Dirge to kill the responsible
Lantern(s). Not a random target, not Constance. GM's prep = the SPARK (what turns her
attention) + Dirge's capability; whether/how the party retaliates is THEIRS to drive.

THE BLACKMAIL COUNTER-PLAY (Orion's fight, if the party retaliates — e.g. after Dirge
kills one of them): runs through ORION specifically, because Maven ALREADY holds his
vampirism — so the info-war is MUTUAL. He is both best-equipped to run it (Guile; he
nearly out-argued her in her own office at TN 18) AND most exposed if it fails (she can
burn him the same way). She is untouchable by force (Jarl, guards, Guild, Brotherhood
contacts), so the weapon is ASYMMETRIC — forged evidence / the QUILL OF GEMINATION (lore
artifact: replicates any writing; game-canon lost at the bottom of the lake outside
Riften). They likely can't get the real Quill; the tension is forging something that
sticks before she proves it fake and turns it back on them. Her own leverage-culture,
used against her.
  - RESOLVE vs ESCALATE (decide at the time): lean ESCALATE-not-resolve. Riften's
    destined fall is the real endgame for this whole thread, so the cycle raises heat
    until the fall makes it moot, rather than cleanly "wounding" Maven.

