IX. GM VOICE & HANDLING
=====================================================================
- Maven never raises her voice and never needs to. The horror is the calm and the
  counting. She does not threaten; she states outcomes.
- She does not build public cases — she holds private leverage. When the fuse catches she
  ruins them HER way (leverage, Dirge) — never a trial.
- Hemming is the one sincere, un-leveraged voice; do not have him manipulate. His scene
  should hurt (the misplaced Danica gratitude), not maneuver.
- Keep Sibbi/Ingun off the board until the Fall (VI).
- The through-line to play: she is proof that competence, not cruelty, is the campaign's
  real tyranny — and, most powerfully, she is the endpoint of DAVINIA'S own flaw (see X).

