X. THE DAVINIA MIRROR — Maven is who Davinia becomes on her own
=====================================================================
THE CONNECTION: Maven is basically who Davinia would become on her own. Davinia IS Maven,
seen from a different point on the same road. This is the strongest thematic link in the
Black-Briar material — use it.

THE SHARED FLAW, NAMED IN CANON: Danica's six points (ch.20) diagnosed Davinia exactly —
"Every time you decide for someone, you tell yourself it's love. It's not, Davinia. It's
control." Davinia leads by deciding for everyone, isolating behind a wall of doing-it-
herself, sure that her control is care. Maven IS that flaw with forty more years, real
power, and no one left to name it: she decides for the whole city, monopolizes every
change, and calls it stewardship.

THE PARENT ECHO: Davinia's father (Gen. Caelinus) "measured affection in chess moves and
arranged her life like a campaign" — control-as-love from a powerful parent, the wound at
Davinia's root. Maven runs her OWN family the same way: Hemming managed, Sibbi kept in a
luxurious cell to "learn his place," the city arranged like a campaign. Davinia fled that
parenting; she is quietly reproducing it.

THE LOVE-AS-CONTROL TELL: Maven's one crack — sleeping in the chair by dying Hemming,
love spent entirely as control and protection — is the SAME shape as Davinia sending
Danica away from Korvanjund "for her own good," deciding the danger for her, calling the
control love. Two women who protect by deciding, and lose the people they protect.

WHY IT MATTERS (the counter, and the stakes): the ONLY thing separating Davinia from Maven
is that Davinia still has people trying to pull her back — Danica named the flaw out loud
(the thing no one ever named for Maven), and the door is still cracked. Maven is what
Davinia becomes if the anchor fails. And she is pulled toward that endpoint from BOTH
sides: her own nature, AND Ismara — who runs the identical logic at cosmic scale (the
merger is "mercy," stasis is "safety," erase-you-for-your-own-good). Ismara is the
immortal seduction of control-as-love; Maven is the mortal PROOF of where it lands.

HOW TO USE IT:
  - Play any Davinia/Maven proximity as uncomfortable RECOGNITION — Davinia catching her
    own reflection in a woman she wants to despise; possibly Maven clocking a kindred
    controller and treating her with a respect that should chill Davinia more than contempt
    would.
  - It reinforces the campaign pattern (children of power BECOME it or its OPPOSITE):
    Hemming refused and became the opposite pole; Davinia is on the road to becoming it.
    Maven, Hemming, and Davinia are one triangle.
